<section xml:id="peer_int_U2">
  <title>Peer Instruction: Using Objects Multiple Choice Questions</title>
  <activity label="bs-objects-2-19">
    <statement>
      <p>What are the components of the second line of code?</p>
      <program language="java">
        <code>
Turtle turtel1 = new Turtle();
turtle1.turn(-45);
        </code>
      </program>
    </statement>

    <choices>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>Type, method/message name, parameter list</p>
        </statement>

        <feedback>
          <p>
            Incorrect. A type can refer to an integer, string, array, or similar
            data type, but that is not what is being referenced in this answer
          </p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>

      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>Class, method/message name, parameter list</p>
        </statement>

        <feedback>
          <p>
            Incorrect. Turtle is the class in this example, but we are not
            calling the class itself in line 2.
          </p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>

      <choice correct="yes">
        <statement>
          <p>Object, method/message name, parameter list</p>
        </statement>

        <feedback>
          <p>
            Correct. turtle1 is created using the Turtle() constructor, and is
            an object of the Turtle class
          </p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
    </choices>
  </activity>
</section>
